results.name: Composite numbers that are the sum of a string of consecutive prime numbers and are divisible by the first and last primes.
comment: Composite n such that n = p_1 + p_2 + ... + p_k where the p_i are consecutive primes and n is divisible by p_1 and p_k.
No more terms below 10^22. - _Michael Beight_, Jul 22 2012
reference: Problem proposed by Carlos Rivera, who found first 4 terms.
example: 503 + 509 + 521+ ... + 508213 = 10225245560, which is divisible by 503 and 508213. - _Manuel Valdivia_, Nov 17 2011
results.author: _Jud McCranie_, Jul 03 2000
ext: a(8) and a(9) from _Michael Beight_, Jul 22 2012
